snippet: The Pacific Northwest Ballet presented four world premieres, three ballets by dancers in the company and one by the Seattle-born Mark Morris.
abstract: Alastair Macaulay reviews dance concert performed by Pacific Northwest Ballet, featuring world premieres by Andrew Bartee, Margaret Mullin, Kiyon Gaines and Mark Morris, at Marion Oliver McCaw Hall in Seattle.
lead_paragraph: The Pacific Northwest Ballet presented four world premieres, three ballets by dancers in the company and one by the Seattle-born Mark Morris.

headline.seo: Pacific Northwest Ballet in Seattle, Mark Morris Premiere
headline.main: In Seattle, a Pride of Choreographers
